\cos(x - \frac{\pi}{2}) = \sin x
y=-\frac{\pi}2
\cos\left(x-\frac{\pi}2\right)=\sin x\;.
\cos(x+y)=\cos x\cos y-\sin x\sin y\;.
\begin{align*} \cos\left(x-\frac{\pi}2\right)&=\cos\left(x+\left(-\frac{\pi}2\right)\right)\\\\ &=\cos x\cos\left(-\frac{\pi}2\right)-\sin x\sin\left(-\frac{\pi}2\right)\\\\ &=\cos x\cdot0-\sin x\cdot(-1)\\\\ &=\sin x\;, \end{align*}
\cos\left(-\dfrac{\pi}2\right)=0
\sin\left(-\dfrac{\pi}2\right)=-1
